annotationA: Probable methylmalonate-semialdehyde dehydrogenase [acylating], mitochondrial; Plays a role in valine and pyrimidine metabolism. Binds fatty acyl-CoA (By similarity); Belongs to the aldehyde dehydrogenase family
annotationB: Probable peroxisomal acyl-coenzyme A oxidase 1; acyl-CoA dehydrogenase activity; flavin adenine dinucleotide binding; acyl-CoA oxidase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: fatty acid oxidation; generation of precursor metabolites and energy; prostaglandin metabolic process; lipid metabolic process; fatty acid beta-oxidation
